Boston is taking a similar road with their efforts towards greener economy. In 2008 the city started creating an action plan to slow down climate change. This green plan refers to reducing the energy consumption of the city, make it greener and more sustainable. Boston is among the few cities that already implemented this action plan with great success. The city has implemented the local green laws enforced among the community towards a “green” living, this is the first stage before completely taking the next step which is converting the local economy towards renewable energy. In Boston, most of the restaurants and shops adopt solar energy as they use the solar powered kitchen appliances and the solar powered LED lights. This makes it easy for the citizens to adapt to the renewable energy and economy as they already use them on a large scale. Today the city is hosting a series of workshops and events educating its citizens and promoting green living and economy.
